  <li id="comment-44934" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Elizabeth</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/11/november-6/#comment-44934"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-01-12T09:20:29-05:00">Tuesday, January 12, 2016 at 9:20 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This cake is AMAZING! I have the roasted applesauce sitting in the fridge waiting for me to make it for the 3rd time in as many weeks tonight. Everyone who has had a slice has loved it. The first time I made it in a bundt pan and it came out great. I followed the recipe exactly but didn&#8217;t use all of the glaze so it could still pass as brunch fare. The second time I made it, my guests came before I had time to glaze it, and it was delicious even when it was naked. I used a loaf pan that I think is 9x5x3. I thought I would have overflow batter for a mini loaf as well, but the batter only filled the loaf pan 3/4-ish of the way, so it was perfectly fine to throw it all in. It had to bake a little longer as a loaf, but my oven is finicky so that may not be the case for all. Absolutely delicious recipe that is now in regular rotation! Thank you thank you Molly!!</p>
    </div>

